SIMPLE: cariama
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: çariama
<hw>⟦cced⟧a`ri*a"ma</hw> <pr>(s⟦aum⟧`r⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧"m⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large,
long-legged cranelike South American wading bird (<spn>Cariama
cristata</spn>, formerly <spn>Dicholophus cristatus</spn>) which preys
upon snakes, etc.; it is also called the <altname>seriema</altname>, but
that latter name is also applied to another South American bird. See
<er>Seriema</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cariama</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cariama
<hw>Cariama</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>The type genus of the
Cariamidae, consisting only of the <spn>Cariama cristata</spn>, also
called the <altname>seriema</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Cariama</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cariamidae</ent>⟦br⟧
